
[1]remains

   REMA'INS, n. plu.

   1. That which is left after a part is separated, taken away or
   destroyed; as the remains of a city or house demolished.

   2. A dead body; a corpse.

   The singular, remain, in the like sense, and in the sense of abode, is
   entirely obsolete.
